+{"id":"frankenredis-sia3","title":"fr-runtime: memory_stats_returns_bulk asserted wrong reply shape","description":"Test was asserting a single bulk-string body with 'key:value' lines; upstream MEMORY STATS replies with a RESP map of bulk-string-key + integer-value pairs. Filed retroactively for fix in 2a22696.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-28T21:33:38.407279215Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-28T21:34:09.856262988Z","closed_at":"2026-04-28T21:34:09.854351728Z","close_reason":"Shipped in 2a22696: rewrote test as memory_stats_returns_keyed_array. Decodes the RESP array, asserts non-empty even-length pair structure, pins canonical upstream-documented keys (peak.allocated, total.allocated, startup.allocated), and pins integer-valued keys to integer replies. cargo test -p fr-runtime --test admin_commands_test 42/42; clippy clean.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
